========================================
 How to compile the source of LS-align
========================================

In Linux system, you can compile the LS-align source as

>cd ./src

>g++ LSalign.cpp -o LSalign

or

>g++ -static -O3 -ffast-math -lm -o LSalign LSalign.cpp

========================================
 How to use LS-align
========================================
In Linux system and the right directory, you can run the program in the command window without arguments to obtain a brief instruction

>./LSalign

Here, an example is shown as follows:

>./LSalign ../example/ace_ligands.mol2 ../example/xtal-lig.mol2



====================
Output Format
====================
QEURY_NAME: the query ligand name
TEMPL_NAME: the template ligand name
PC-score8Q:	the PC-score if normalized by atom number of Query Ligand
PC-score8T: the PC-score if normalized by atom number of Template Ligand
Pval_PC8Q:	the P-value of PC-score8Q based on statistic (Gumbel distribution)
Pval_PC8T:	the P-value of PC-score8T based on statistic (Gumbel distribution)
JaccardR:		the Jaccard ratio of this alignment 
RMSD_LS:		the RMSD_LS of this alignment
QUERY_SIZE: The atom number (without 'H') of the query ligand
TEMPL_SIZE: The atom number (without 'H') of the template ligand

(Some detail definitions can be found at http://zhanglab.ccmb.med.umich.edu/LS-align/ReportParam.html)

